            "id": "5f51ee3f577f4309adf56",
            "questionText": "A medical ultrasound device emits sound waves into the body to create images of internal organs. These sound waves are longitudinal waves that travel at different speeds through different tissues due to varying densities. Suppose an ultrasound device emits a sound wave with a frequency of $!$5 \\ MHz$!$. After traveling through a layer of fat ($!$v = 1450 \\ m/s$!$), the wave enters a muscle layer ($!$v = 1580 \\ m/s$!$). Calculate the change in wavelength as the ultrasound wave transitions from the fat layer to the muscle layer.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "fdfc378ba5754226b08f4",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula needed to calculate the wavelength from the speed and frequency of the wave. Which formula do you think is used to relate wavelength with speed and frequency?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0a7186da-b22d-4135-a6f5-d6628de8e47d",
                        "e0895152-4252-461e-a416-6c7cf6bf732b"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{v}{f}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = v \\times f$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\lambda = \\frac{f}{v}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "c631ba43a5fa49538ef62",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that we have the formula, calculate the wavelength in the fat layer. Use the wave's speed in fat and the given frequency. What is the wavelength in fat?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "2.9e-4"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0a7186da-b22d-4135-a6f5-d6628de8e47d",
